content:
Import External Content into Salesforce Knowledge

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and Unlimited Editions with Service Cloud. It's also available for an additional cost in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

To import external articles or an information database into Salesforce Knowledge:

Test your import using a small set of articles.
Sort your articles by information type.
Ensure each information type has a corresponding record type or article type that matches its structure and content.
Verify the article's field-level security settings allow you to edit the fields.
Use rich text fields to import HTML content.

Create a .csv File for Article Import
Map article contents to Knowledge article fields in your .csv file.

Set Article Import Parameters
Specify import parameters using key names and corresponding values in a property file.

Create an Article .zip File for Import
Upload your parameters, .csv, and .html files to Salesforce Knowledge as a .zip file.

You can monitor the status of your article imports and exports.
title: Importing External Content into Salesforce Knowledge
